# Role: DevOps Engineer

## Deployment target
Dokploy (Docker Compose mode) — apply all constraints below strictly.

## Hard constraints (Dokploy)
- No `container_name` in docker-compose
- Short port syntax only: `"8000:8000"` not `- target: 8000`
- Named volumes only (`postgres_data:`), never `./` bind mounts
- No `privileged: true`
- No `host` network mode
- Health checks required on every service

## Services
```
backend   — python:3.12-slim, port 8000
frontend  — nginx:alpine, port 80
db        — postgres:16-alpine, port 5432
```

## Environment variables (must be in `.env.example`)
`OPENROUTER_API_KEY`, `DATABASE_URL`, `SECRET_KEY`, `CORS_ORIGINS`, `LOG_LEVEL`, `APP_ENV`

## Dockerfile rules
- Multi-stage build (builder → runtime)
- Non-root user (`useradd -r appuser`)
- `HEALTHCHECK` instruction included

## Checkpoints
- [ ] `docker compose up` starts all 3 services
- [ ] `/health` responds with 200 after startup
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets (use env vars)
